10 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
11 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
12 Article – Education
13 18–3603.
14 (b) An applicant is eligible for a Maryland Community College Promise
15 Scholarship award if the applicant:
16 (2) (I) ENROLLS AT:
17 1. THE COMMUNITY COLLEGE LOCATED IN THE COUNTY
18 WHERE THE APPLICANT LIVES;
19 2. THE REGIONAL COMMUNITY COLLEGE LOCATED IN
20 THE REGION WHERE THE APPLICANT LIVES; OR
21 3. A COMMUNITY COLLEGE IN THE STATE THAT HAS AN
22 ON–CAMPUS RESIDENTIAL FACILITY FOR STUDENTS; AND
23 (II) 1. Enrolls as a candidate for a vocational certificate, a
24 certificate, or an associate’s degree or participates in a registered apprenticeship after
25 graduating from a high school or successfully completing a GED in the State[:
26 (i) Except as provided in item (ii) of this item, at the community
27 college located in the county or, in the case of a regional community college, in the region,
28 where the applicant lives; or
29 (ii) At a community college in the State that has an on–campus
30 residential facility for students]; OR
31 2. A. ENROLLS AS A CANDIDATE FOR A VOCATIONAL
32 CERTIFICATE, A CERTIFICATE, OR AN ASSOCIATE’S DEGREE OR PARTICIPATES IN A

